'''Carlos Joaquim Antunes dos Santos'''<ref name="cmjornal"/> ({{IPA|pt|ˈkaɾ.luʒ ʒu.ɐ.ˈkĩ ɐ̃.ˈtu.nɨʒ duʃ ˈsɐ̃.tuʃ|lang}}; born 24 August 2000), known as '''"CJ" '''{{IPA|en|si˸ ʤeɪ|lang}} '''dos Santos''' is a <!-- Do not refer to him as American, Cape Verdean or Portuguese. --> professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[San Diego FC]]. Born in the United States, he plays for the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]]. <!--As he's applied for a one-time switch, he's cap-tied to Cape Verde and can no longer represent the United States.-->

==Club career==
Dos Santos began playing football at the age of 2, and continued his development with local football academies Foxchase SC, Philadelphia SC, and FC Delco before moving to [[Philadelphia Union]] in 2013. In August 2016, he signed with the academy of [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in Portugal.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/players/d/cj-dos-santos |title=CJ Dos Santos &#124; U.S. Soccer Official Website |website=ussoccer.com}}</ref> Dos Santos made his professional debut with [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]] in a 1–1 [[Liga Portugal 2]] tie with [[F.C. Porto B]] on 25 January 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/01/25/portugal/liga-de-honra/porto-b/benfica-b/3355136/ |title=Porto II vs. Benfica II - 25 January 2021 - Soccerway |website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref>

On 11 February 2022, dos Santos signed with [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Inter Miami CF|Inter Miami]].<ref>{{cite web |date=February 11, 2022 |title=Inter Miami CF sign goalkeeper CJ dos Santos from Benfica |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/inter-miami-cf-sign-goalkeeper-cj-dos-santos-from-benfica |access-date=February 11, 2022 |publisher=Major League Soccer}}</ref>

On 11 December 2024, dos Santos signed with Major League Soccer club [[San Diego FC]].<ref>{{cite web |date=February 11, 2022 |title=San Diego FC acquire CJ dos Santos from Inter Miami |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/san-diego-fc-acquire-cj-dos-santos-from-inter-miami |access-date=December 11, 2024 |publisher=Major League Soccer}}</ref>

==International career==
Dos Santos was born in [[Philadelphia]] to a [[Cape Verde]]an father and a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] mother.<ref name="cmjornal">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/detalhe/cj-dos-santos-a-promessa-do-benfica-que-ambiciona-chegar-a-champions |title='CJ' dos Santos, a promessa do Benfica que ambiciona chegar à 'Champions' |website=cmjornal.pt}}</ref> He was a youth international for the United States, having represented the [[United States men's national under-17 soccer team|United States U17]]s at the [[2017 CONCACAF U-17 Championship]] and [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].<ref name="auto"/> He was called up for a training camp for the senior [[United States men's national soccer team]] in December 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.onegoal.us/articles/2020/12/5/december-camp-spotlight-cj-dos-santos |title=December Camp Spotlight: CJ Dos Santos |website=OneGoal USMNT Soccer News, Analysis, and Email Newsletter}}</ref>

He was one of the players who were selected with the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]] for the [[Exhibition match|friendly]] matches against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] and [[Finland national football team|Finland]] on 27 and 30 March 2026, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/federacaocaboverdianafutebol|title=O Selecionador Nacional, Pedro Brito 'Bubista', apresentou a lista dos convocados para o FIFA Series, a realizar-se na Nova Zelândia.|publisher=[[Cape Verdean Football Federation]]|date=19 March 2026|language=pt}}</ref>

On 13 May 2026, dos Santos' request to switch allegiance to Cape Verde was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change">{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|accessdate=May 13, 2026}}</ref> On 18 May, he was called up by Cape Verde's head coach [[Bubista]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/articles/cabo-verde-squad-announcement-world-cup-bubista</ref><ref>https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/fifa-world-cup-2026/articles/bubista-s-official-cabo-verde-squad-for-the-2026-fifa-world-cup-2026-05-19</ref>

